Description: The BeautyDirect platform will be implemented as a managed services platform to complement.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: A few important, but overlooked operational tasks particularly in the professional sector of the beauty supply and cosmetics industry involve accessing a just-in-time inventory replenishment system, negotiating factory-direct pricing, verifying upstream product sources, and implementing effective anti-diversion solutions. Atlanta-based NHC Beauty Enterprises, Inc. d/b/a NSP Intelligence, Inc. (NSPIntel) has embarked on an ambitious project to design and implement a managed services platform called BeautyDirect. The vision behind BeautyDirect is that it will be an integrated supply chain management system designed to secure, simplify and enable efficient purchasing integration for beauty and cosmetics businesses not owned by a mega-chain.  The BeautyDirect platform will be implemented as a managed services platform to complement and extend routine inventory management tasks at the salon level, and up to the raw materials level.  The beauty and cosmetics industry has experienced explosive growth over the years, but in many parts of the industry, it is still siloed, in some cases paper-based, and is very inefficient using its present disparate processes and methodologies. Beauty and cosmetics industry players face many competitive and operational challenges as part of doing business; by implementing an integrated system that has a solid foundation based on strong product manufacturer partnerships, the goal is to create a secure supply chain, improve the distribution process, and control as much of the distribution workflow as best efforts allow. Best-practice supply chain management features in BeautyDirect are envisioned to help connect consumer trends with product development, mitigate product diversion risks, enhance partner collaboration, improve distribution operations, and enable a seamless workflow across raw materials, manufacturing, distribution, and consumer sales.

Description: Music America was as a vision for a new type of music company. This type of music company would have digital distribution, music
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Music America was as a vision for a new type of music company. This type of music company would have digital distribution, music publishing, marketing and management all done online, with the artist at the center. The company comprised three divisions: Music America Recording, Music America Publishing and Music Technology.   Music America Recording failed to take off. The music technology relaunched as Bluewire, which was a platform for artists to connect, market and sell directly to their fans. Each music artist would create their own fan club through Bluewire which they would manage. The social networking features drew the attention of other non-music clients who customized the platform for use in education, sports and general purpose social networking.  Music America Publishing became Praise Collection which acquired the rights to thousands of hours of rare, live performances featuring some of the world's most famous gospel and country artists including Chet Atkins, CeCe Winans, Fred Hammond, Yolanda Adams and many others. The performances were compiled into a subscription DVD service and sold through direct marketing channels.  The three divisions, which became three separate companies, eventually all closed and were dissolved.
Industry Groups: Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio
